Package: gplite
Title: Lightweight Implementation for the Most Common Gaussian Process Models
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(person("Juho", "Piironen", role = c("cre", "aut"), email = "juho.t.piironen@gmail.com"))
Description: 
  Implements the most common Gaussian process (GP) models using Laplace approximation, 
  maximum marginal likelihood inference for the hyperparameters, and sparse
  approximations for larger datasets. In addition, provides also convenient 
  interface to perform Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) inference for the latent values with 
  fixed hyperparameters using Stan probabilistic programming language. 
Depends: 
  R (>= 3.4.0),
